Secondly, if there is such a virus in hedgehogs how would it survive
the reality that such a (?chronic) infection and progressive
neurological lesions will soon result in a hedgehog being lunch for a
fox or a badger, and termination of the infection? A number of
solutions come to mind, e.g., either that many are called (infected)
but few are chosen (for lesions); or that the length of the infection
does not significantly impact overall fertility; or that the
infections have spilt over from the natural reservoir into hedgehogs
